           SPELL=kavi2svcd
         VERSION=0.5.5
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-${VERSION}.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}-${VERSION}
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.cornelinux.de/linux/kavi2svcd/dl/$SOURCE
          MD5[0]=e12ae557c0b4bc31dd0ac0c62b3c7241
        WEB_SITE=http://www.cornelinux.de/linux/$SPELL/index-english.html
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
         ENTERED=20030116
         UPDATED=20030116
      MAINTAINER=eschabell@sourcemage.org
           SHORT="GUI for generating MPEG files from an AVI file."
cat << EOF

kavi2svcd is a GUI for generating MPEG files from an AVI file using 
transcode and mplex. It then generates a Video CD image using vcdimager 
and burns to CD with cdrdao. It can generate m1v, m2v, and mpa files, 
multiplex the MPEG file, generate cue and bin files, and allows the 
generated command lines to be edited before executing them. 

EOF
